HEADWORD: Planaria
<hw>Pla*na"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
L. <plw>Planari⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, E. <plw>-rias</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL. See <er>Planary</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any species of turbellarian worms belonging to
<gen>Planaria</gen>, and many allied genera. The body is usually flat,
thin, and smooth. Some species, in warm countries, are
terrestrial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

